Job Overview:
Acting as a key member of the Engineering Team, part of the Execution, Engineer will be responsible for the preparation of the engineering documents of the assigned projects by coordinating the specific functions of the engineering team. Consistently coordinate the assigned engineering team to complete the overall project’s design in compliance with the project schedule and within the budget; observing the correctness and the completeness of the provided information.
Goals:
• Guarantee the delivery of the engineering documents package within the schedule and budget agreed with the PM;
• Coordinate the functions of the engineering team distributing the tasks and tracking the progress with attention to keep the team interacting and motivated;
• Ensure the application of highest safety standards and reduce the project impacts to the environment by organizing overall design review of the assigned projects;
• Meet / improve the project schedule;
• Meet / improve the quality standards;
• Identify and submit possibly “cost-effective” improvements in the design.
Key Responsibilities Include:
Tasks include:
• Collect from the Project contract and the Project Manager all the information needed to organize the project team and assign specific tasks for the design of the project;
• Prepare related document and estimated cost of mechanical works.
• Design piping & fabrication equipment design.
• Issue inquiry & prepare technical evaluation for mechanical part: fabrication equipment & mechanical site works.
• Plan and coordinate the engineering activities for all assigned projects and monitor the activities progress in compliance with the schedule defined on the general document list;
• Review the deliverables prepared by the specific functions and ensure the quality standards, the correctness and the consistency of the documents to be transmitted to both clients and contractors;
• Organize design reviews, risk assessments and coordination meetings as needed by the specific design;
• Join the FAT and the SAT of the plant, sustaining Commissioning Engineer and the Project Manager about engineering topics, also by assigning tasks to the functions part of the engineering team;
• Precisely record costs and hours spent in the engineering activities so to guarantee each project budget assigned;

